disnet 0.0.0.9000
  • Reference

Main simulation function

Source: R/simulation.R
disnet_simulate.Rd

This function wraps up all simulation sub-functins and applies them to the intermediate sim files (created by `disnet_sim_setup`

disnet_simulate(nsims = 10, nsteps = 1000, sim_input = sim_intermed,
  sim_output_dir = getOption("disnetOutputDir", NA), parallel = FALSE,
  seed = 0)

Arguments

nsims

The number of simulations to run. Default is 10
nsteps

The number of timesteps you'd like each simulation to run for. Default = 1000. It's set to a large value so that outbreaks can run their course.
sim_input

The file setup/created by disnet_sim_setup, which has incorprated the foi, infection seeding, and/or vaccination campaign.
sim_output_dir

The directory you'd like to save the simulation results to.

Examples

f = system.file("sampleData", "g.rds", package = "disnet")
g = readRDS(f)
g_comm = disnet_commuting(g)
